commit.message:
Fix small typo / grammatical error

For info on practice vs. practise, see: https://www.dictionary.com/e/practice-vs-practise/

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Changed MatchParen colors to use the once from Search.

This makes Brackets Match much more visible.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Fix underlined CursorLineNr in gutter

Vim started underlining the CursorLineNr in the gutter (":set number",
":set cursorline") from 8.1.2029 and onwards. Remove this by forcing our
own cterm definition without underlining instead.

Note, that you'll need to restart Vim for this change to take effect.
Simply sourcing the color scheme file won't do.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Use new :terminal coloring for Vim 8.2.0+

Only apply the new ANSI colors for Vim >= 8.2.0.
Other versions use the old method with the "Terminal" highlight group.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Support for less jumpy line numbers

If you use line numbering (i.e. ":set number"), and want to make the
line numbers go more to the background, use:

   let g:zenburn_subdued_LineNr=1.

Thanks to Ledohod for reporting this.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>
add setting g:zenburn_disable_bold_CursorBars

Add initial :terminal coloring

The terminal was not colored like the rest of the Vim, change them to be
close to colors used by Zenburn.

Right now the color order is as usually used in the terminal (black,
red, green, yellow, ...). It might make sense to tint the terminal
towards one or two colors but that shall be for future work.

Coloring the terminal Vim seems to need ":set termguicolors".

Terminal coloring feature works in at least Vim 8.2.0+ but seems
generally buggy; I've not seen the high 7 colors used.

Fixes #30

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

README: Host screenshot on Github

To save some bandwidth, avoid downloading the screenshot directly from
the Zenburn page at kippura.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>
chore: Add screenshot to readme

commit.message: obey zenburn_italic_Comment in gui mode

Support italic Comment

To use italic Comment, use let g:zenburn_italic_Comment=1 prior to
loading the colorscheme.

Note: not all terminals support cterm=italic, if the support is missing,
the terminal output will look weird.

Fixes #26.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Converted readme to markdown

Converted plain text readme to markdown.

Alternate new-style visual for terminal

The closest color I'm happy with is 23, although it's blue instead of
green. But it's roughly the same "feel".

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>
Enable alternate new-style Visual

Support Conceal syntax group

This was unintentionally omitted, add it.

Fixes #22.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Support terminal coloring in Vim 8

Vim 8 supports the new :terminal command. Zenburn had no color support
for it yet, so add it.

Note: the system colors (set e.g. via LS_COLORS in Linux) will be shown
in the terminal window. The highlight setting only overrides the
"default" color.

Fixes #21.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Highlight and copy to clipboard w/o a line break

To reduce potential confusion.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Don't display variable names in bold

Solve issue in the terminal version: don't display variable names in
bold.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Update zenburnpage URL

Blog host has moved, update to the new zenburnpage URL.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Deprecating the version string

At v2.25 (this version) the version string present in zenburn.vim is
deprecated since it's a bother to keep a hardcoded version string in the
file. Going forward, the versioning will use annotated tags instead.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Fix Visual and Error

* add term highlights for Visual and VisualNOS
* make Error bold in gui

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Bump up the version number

As of now taking the version number up is manually done like in this
commit. The number itself is for the benefit of people who do not see
the git history.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Fix up CursorLineNr

After the previous fixes, the CursorLineNr was a bit too dark.
The dark colour could be seen with:

set cursorline
set number

This change aligns the CursorLineNr with the old look-and-feel and
fine-tunes it to also be slightly duller than before. The change applies
both to the UI and console colors.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nurminen <slinky@iki.fi>

Merge pull request #10 from holomorph/collect-defns

Original comments from holomorph:
"This is a refactor which gets rid of a lot of logic and lines by combining the gui and term highlights. There are very few visible changes to the theme, and these changes are made only in the interest of making the colorscheme more complete or consistent between gui and term.

With these changes (the gui and term colors for a syntax group being on the same line), it is much easier to spot missing/inconsistent pieces of the colorscheme."

IMO the CursorLineNr is now too dim, but since this set of patches is just great, a new patch will be made for CursorLineNr a bit later. Thanks a lot!
